**who —** VALVE STEAM DECK — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown

**what —** Valve's handheld is a full x86 PC you hold: an AMD Zen 2 / RDNA 2 chip running Linux-based SteamOS, with a desktop mode, full controls, and the ability to install almost anything. It reframed the handheld not as a closed console but as a portable computer that plays a PC library.

**where —** the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored  Framework inputs: the chips; the buses; the spec; the lore  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** Valve's handheld is a full x86 PC you hold: an AMD Zen 2 / RDNA 2 chip running Linux-based SteamOS, with a desktop mode, full controls, and the ability to install almost anything. It reframed the handheld not as a closed console but as a portable computer that plays a PC library.

